  				<tr>
  					<td align=center valign="top" width=100%><br>
  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table width=75% border=0 cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0 align=center>  <tr>
    <td width='100%' align='left' valign='top' bgcolor='#0E024D' colspan=5 class='spti2'>WIZARD FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db2' colspan=2>Click <a href=faq.asp?Action=SubmitQ>Here</a> To Submit A Frequently Asked Question<hr size='1'></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>What level do wizards not have to press the meditate button anymore?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>After Level 35 it is no longer necessary to use your book to meditate.  Just by sitting down you will automatically use your skill to regain mana faster.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>What is the best race for a wizard? Erudite, High Elf, Gnome or Dark elf? </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>There is no one race which is best.  All of them have advantages and disadvantages.  Take a look at our Wizard creation guide for a full explanation.  You can find it <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/creationguides/wizard.asp'><b>here</b></a>.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>When do Wizzy's Get their Self-Only Port to WC? I Didn't see it in with the others at Lvl 20.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>At level 24.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>Do wizards get a pet a any point in the game?
</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>Flaming Sword of Xuzl is a level 59 wizard spell.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>I have a wizard that is currently level 4. I dont have meditate. What gives?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>All pure casters should recieve meditate at level four. The player must train a point in meditate at his guild for it to go into effect.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>Is it true that a wizard can regenerate mana quicker by drinking alcohol and allowing his intelligence to decrease, then he does by meditating?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>When a character drinks alcohol, it lowers the intelligence thus making it appear that he has more mana. One can get full mana faster, but not the normal amount they would have while sober. </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>What trade skill would be best for a Wizard to focus his time on?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>All trade skills have some commercial value.  Jewellery tends to be the most valuable, but it is very competitive, and expensive to learn.<P>
Pottery has good sale value to rogues for vials, and tailoring for 10 slot backpacks.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>Where can I find some runes?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>Runes are often found on monsters throughout Norrath. Most runes needed for  researching spells can be found on the monsters equal to the spell level up to five levels above it. Merchants frequently carry these as well. </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>Why was the spell Alter Plane: Fear removed from the game?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>Fear was populated differently from the original design.  This meant that there was no need for this spell and it was removed.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>Why do they make monsters agro on Wizards so often?  Isn't bad enuff we have no hp or ac?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>I think Enchanters and Bards and Rangers would probably all ask the same thing.  Different factors effect an NPC's hate list, if you are being hit too much slow down your chain burns to allow the tanks to taunt.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>Why don't wizards have more stunning spells?  Root is ok but too unpredictable when going solo.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>Wizards get sufficient stuns for their role in groups.  Remember no class in EverQuest is purely a solo class, and you should learn to use your spells effectively within groups in order to be the best player possible.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>This is a question I am dying to know, At level 60 wizards get a spell &#34;Disentigrate&#34; and it is supposidley a banishment spell. Does this mean that there will be no corpse, and no exp, or what?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>That is correct this spell literally destroys the target.  It is an emergency use spell.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>What lvl do wizard spells get resisted ?
</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>Beginning at level one, any monster can resist any spells. Usually, a monster five or more levels higher than the caster will resist, without a debuff.  </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>Why do some of my spells not hit the target sometimes?
</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>There are two reasons.<P>
Bolt spells require a direct unimpeded line of site to the target.  This includes players, pets, NPC's or objects.  Anything which gets in the way will block the spell.<P>
The other more general case is when you cannot see your target.  The engine shots an invisible beam from the middle of your body to the middle of the enemy and if there is any wall or object in the way, or if one of the two are in water and the other isn't, then you will not be able to see or damage your target.<P>
In both these cases mana will still be consumed.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>When should Wizards stop using weapons?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>Wizards should generally use weapons for some added damage up until level 25 to 30.  It depends on the mob you are attacking and the group you are with, but any extra damage is always going to help.<P>
Meleeing is also an important part of raising your defense skill which protects you a great deal at later levels.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db' colspan=2 align=right><a class='db2'href=faq.asp?Action=Show&Class=Wizard&Page=2><b>Next Page</b></a></td>
  </tr>
